{{wikipediapar|Logical fallacy}}
==English==

===Noun===
'''logic fallacy'''  (''plural:'' '''[[logic fallacies]]''')
# Clearly defined error in reasoning used to support or refute an argument, excluding simple unintended mistakes.
#:"You can't prove Santa doesn't exist, therefore Santa does exist", is a common [[logic fallacy]].

===Alternative spellings===
*[[logical fallacy]]

===Usage note===
Logic fallacies are typically given Latin names.  Eg, ''Argumentum ad ignorantiam''